<TITLE> Chittagong polls set for first e-vote </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, June 10 (bdnews24.com)  Last minute preparations for Bangladesh's first ever electronic voting are taking place. The Chittagong City Corporation elections set on June 17 will host the first e-voting pilot scheme at ward 21 in Jamalkhan. The Election Commission is set to introduce digital voting with voting equipment already arriving at the port city election office, the election's assistant returning officer Farhad Hossain told bdnews24.com on Wednesday. The concerned presiding, assistant presiding and polling officers will be briefed on the new voting system on Thursday, he said. The EC last week received 130 Electronic Voting Machines (EVMs) from Bangladesh University of Engineering and Technology. Some EVMs have been made ready for the trial voting with installation of dummy candidates and symbols. EC senior assistant secretary (municipality) Abdul Baten told bdnews24.com last week that there would be 79 booths under 14 voting centres at ward number 21, with 25,230 voters  12,879 males and 12,351 females. He said names and symbols of the candidates would be installed on June 4-5 in 93 EVMs, of which 79 would be set in booths as the other 14 remain as back-up. Baten said 37 voting machines, reserved for trial and training, would not be used during the election. bdn
